      <text xml:space="preserve">{{About|the Northern constellation|the astronomical observatory|BOOTES}}
{{Infobox Constellation
| name = Boötes
| abbreviation = Boo
| genitive = Boötis
| pronounce = {{IPA-en|boʊˈoʊtiːz|}}, genitive {{IPA|/boʊˈoʊtɨs/}}&lt;ref&gt;[[OED]]&lt;/ref&gt;
| symbolism = the herdsman
| RA = 15
| dec= +30
| family = [[Ursa Major Family|Ursa Major]]
| quadrant = NQ3
| areatotal = 907
| arearank = 13th
| numbermainstars = 7, 15
| numberbfstars = 59
| numberstarsplanets = 8
| numberbrightstars = 3
| numbernearbystars = 3
| brighteststarname = [[Arcturus]] (α Boo)
| starmagnitude = −0.04
| neareststarname = [[Wolf 498]]
| stardistancely = 17.71
| stardistancepc = 5.43
| numbermessierobjects = 0
| meteorshowers = [[January Bootids]]&lt;br /&gt;[[June Bootids]]&lt;br /&gt;[[Quadrantids]]
| bordering = [[Canes Venatici]]&lt;br /&gt;[[Coma Berenices]]&lt;br /&gt;[[Corona Borealis]]&lt;br /&gt;[[Draco (constellation)|Draco]]&lt;br /&gt;[[Hercules (constellation)|Hercules]]&lt;br /&gt;[[Serpens|Serpens Caput]]&lt;br /&gt;[[Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]]&lt;br /&gt;[[Ursa Major]]
| latmax = [[North Pole|90]]
| latmin = [[50th parallel south|50]]
| month = June
| notes='''Other designations:''' Arctophylax}}
'''Boötes''' ({{IPA-en|boʊˈoʊtiːz|US}} {{IPA-en|bəʊˈəʊtiːz|UK}}, or boh-'oh-tees&lt;ref&gt;http://www.space.com/spacewatch/lc_pronunciation.html&lt;/ref&gt;) is a [[constellation]] in the northern sky, located between 0° and +60° [[declination]], and 13 and 16 hours of [[right ascension]] on the [[celestial sphere]]. The name comes from the [[Greek language|Greek]] Βοώτης, ''Boōtēs'', meaning [[herder|herdsman]] or [[plowman]] (literally, ox-driver; from ''boos'', related to the [[Latin language|Latin]] ''bovis'', “cow”). The &quot;ö&quot; in the name is a [[Diaeresis (diacritic)|diaeresis]], not an [[Umlaut (diacritic)|umlaut]], meaning that each 'o' is to be pronounced separately.

Boötes was one of the 48 [[constellation]]s described by the 2nd century astronomer [[Ptolemy]] and is now one of the 88 modern [[constellation]]s. It contains the [[List of brightest stars|third brightest star]] in the night sky, [[Arcturus]].

== Notable features ==
===Stars===
[[Tau Boötis|τ Boötis]], a relatively [[Sun]]-like star, is orbited by the massive [[hot Jupiter]] planet [[Tau Boötis Ab|τ Boötis Ab]]. It was the fourth [[extrasolar planet]] to be discovered and is one of the most studied. Boötes also hosts a large number of double stars suitable for viewing by amateur astronomers.{{Citation needed|date=April 2011}}

====Named stars====
{{See also|List of stars in Boötes}}
{| class=&quot;wikitable&quot;
