* [[Johann Friedrich Fasch]]: Several bassoon concerti; the best known is in C major
* [[Christoph Graupner]]: [[List of concertos by Christoph Graupner|Four bassoon concerti]]
* [[Johann Wilhelm Hertel]]: Bassoon Concerto in A minor
* [[Georg Philipp Telemann]]: Sonata in F minor
* [[Antonio Vivaldi]]: 39 concerti for bassoon, 37 of which exist in their entirety today
* [[Jan Dismas Zelenka]]: Six trio sonatas for two oboes, bassoon and [[Figured bass|basso continuo]]

===Classical===
* [[Johann Christian Bach]]: Bassoon Concerto in B{{Music|b}}, Bassoon Concerto in E{{Music|b}} major
* [[Franz Danzi]]: Bassoon Concertos in G minor, in C, two in F major)
* [[François Devienne]]: Twelve Sonatas (six with opus numbers), three Quartets, one Concerto, six Duos Concertants
* [[Johann Nepomuk Hummel]]: Grand Concerto for Bassoon (in F)
* [[Leopold Kozeluch]]: Bassoon Concertos in B{{Music|b}} major (P V:B1) and C major (P V:C1)
* [[Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart]]: [[Bassoon Concerto (Mozart)|Bassoon Concerto]] in B{{Music|b}}, K. 191, the only surviving of the original three bassoon concertos he wrote
* [[Antonio Rosetti]]: Bassoon Concertos in F major (Murray C75), in B{{Music|b}} major (Murray C69, C73, C74), in E{{Music|b}} major (Murray C68) &lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|title=Rosetti Bassoon Concertos — Catalog and Track Listing|publisher=Naxos Records|url=http://www.naxos.com/catalogue/item.asp?item_code=8.555341|year=2003|accessdate=7 September 2008}} The E{{Music|b}} concerto is mentioned in the notes to the recording, see the link on the left.&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Carl Stamitz]]: Bassoon Concerto in F major
* [[Johann Baptist Vanhal]]: Bassoon Concerto in C major, and Concerto in F major for two bassoons and orchestra

===Romantic===
* [[Franz Berwald]]: Konzertstueck
* [[Ferdinand David (musician)|Ferdinand David]]: Concertino for bassoon and orchestra, op. 12
* [[Edward Elgar]]: [[Romance for bassoon (Elgar)|Romance for bassoon and orchestra]], op. 62
* [[Johann Fuchs]]: Bassoon Concerto in B{{Music|b}} major
* [[Julius Fučík (composer)|Julius Fučík]]: ''Der alte Brummbär'' (&quot;The Old Grumbler&quot;) for bassoon and orchestra, op. 210
* [[Reinhold Glière]]: Humoresque and Impromptu for Bassoon and Piano, op. 35, nos. 8 and 9
* [[Camille Saint-Saëns]]: Sonata for bassoon and piano in G major, op. 168
* [[Carl Maria von Weber]]: Andante e rondo ungarese in C minor, op. 35; [[Bassoon Concerto (Weber)|Bassoon Concerto in F, op. 75]]

===Twentieth century===
