===Pieces featuring famous bassoon passages===
* [[Béla Bartók]]: [[Concerto for Orchestra (Bartók)|Concerto for Orchestra]]; the second movement features woodwind instruments in pairs, beginning with the bassoons, and the recapitulation of their duet adds a third instrument playing a staccato counter-melody.
* [[Ludwig van Beethoven]]: [[Symphony No. 4 (Beethoven)|Symphony No. 4 in B{{Music|b}} major]], [[Symphony No. 9 (Beethoven)|Symphony 9 in D minor]], last movement
* [[Hector Berlioz]]: ''[[Symphonie fantastique]]'' (In the fourth movement, there are several solo and [[tutti]] bassoon-featuring passages. This piece calls for four bassoons.)
* [[Georges Bizet]]: ''[[Carmen]]'', Entr'acte to Act II
* [[Paul Dukas]]: ''[[The Sorcerer's Apprentice (Dukas)|The Sorcerer's Apprentice]]'', widely recognized as used in the movie ''[[Fantasia (film)|Fantasia]]''; the main melody is first heard in a famous bassoon soli passage.
* [[Edvard Grieg]]: ''[[In the Hall of the Mountain King]]''
* [[Carl Orff]]: ''[[Carmina Burana (Orff)|Carmina Burana]]'' (the 12th movement, &quot;Olim lacus colueram&quot;, opens with a high bassoon solo; it is nicknamed &quot;The Swan&quot;)
* [[Sergei Prokofiev]]: ''[[Peter and the Wolf]]'' (possibly the most-recognized bassoon theme, the part of the grandfather)
* [[Maurice Ravel]]: ''[[Rapsodie espagnole|Rapsodie Espagnole]]'' (features a fast, lengthy dual [[cadenza]] at the end of the first movement), [[Boléro]] (the bassoon has a high descending solo passage near the beginning), [[Piano Concerto (Ravel)|Piano Concerto in G Major]], Piano Concerto in D Major (for the left hand) prominent use of contrabassoon in the opening, ''[[Ma Mère l'Oie]]'' a contrabassoon solo in the fourth part
* [[Nikolai Rimsky-Korsakov]]: ''[[Scheherazade (Rimsky-Korsakov)|Scheherazade]]'', second movement
* [[Dmitri Shostakovich]]: Several symphonies including [[Symphony No. 1 (Shostakovich)|#1]], [[Symphony No. 4 (Shostakovich)|4]], [[Symphony No. 5 (Shostakovich)|5]], [[Symphony No. 7 (Shostakovich)|7 (Leningrad)]] (first movement), [[Symphony No. 8 (Shostakovich)|8]], &amp; [[Symphony No. 9 (Shostakovich)|9]],
* [[Jean Sibelius]]: [[Symphony No. 5 (Sibelius)|Symphony 5 in E{{Music|b}} major]]
* [[Igor Stravinsky]]: ''[[The Rite of Spring]]'' (opens with a famously unorthodox bassoon solo), lullaby from ''[[The Firebird]]'', ''[[Pulcinella Suite]]''
* [[Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky]]: [[Symphony No. 4 (Tchaikovsky)|Symphony 4 in F minor]], [[Symphony No. 5 (Tchaikovsky)|Symphony 5 in E minor]], [[Symphony No. 6 (Tchaikovsky)|Symphony 6 in B minor]]
* [[Modest Mussorgsky]]: ''[[Pictures at an Exhibition]]'' orchestrated by Maurice Ravel
* [[Gaetano Donizetti]]: ''[[Una furtiva lagrima]]'', from the Italian opera, ''[[L'elisir d'amore]]'' (opens with a solo bassoon passage)

