'''''Buffy the Vampire Slayer''''' is a 1992 American  [[Action film|action]]/[[Comedy film|comedy]]/[[horror film]] about a [[Valley girl]] [[Cheerleading|cheerleader]] named [[Buffy Summers|Buffy]] ([[Kristy Swanson]]) who learns that it is her fate to hunt [[vampires]]. The original [[script (recorded media)|script]] for the film was written by [[Joss Whedon]], who later created the darker and more acclaimed [[Buffy the Vampire Slayer (TV series)|TV series of the same name]] starring [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]] as Buffy. It was a moderate success at the box office&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=weekend&amp;id=buffythevampireslayer.htm|title=Buffy the Vampire Slayer (1992) Weekend Box Office|work=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=2007-04-19}}&lt;/ref&gt; and received mixed reviews from critics.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/buffy_the_vampire_slayer/|title=Buffy the Vampire Slayer (1992)|work=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=February 6, 2007}}&lt;/ref&gt;

==Plot==
[[Buffy Summers|Buffy]] ([[Kristy Swanson]]) is a stereotypical [[Cheerleading|cheerleader]] at Hemery High School in [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]]. She is a carefree popular girl whose main concerns are shopping and spending time with her friends. While at school one day, she is approached by a man named [[Minor characters of Buffy the Vampire Slayer#Merrick|Merrick Jamison-Smythe]] ([[Donald Sutherland]]). He informs her that she is [[Slayer (Buffyverse)|The Slayer]], or chosen one, and he is a Watcher whose duty it is to guide and train her. She initially refuses to believe his claims, but becomes convinced when he is able to describe a recurring dream of hers in great detail. Over the course of her training she becomes friends with [[List of minor Buffy the Vampire Slayer characters#Pike|Oliver Pike]] ([[Luke Perry]]), whose best friend has recently become a vampire. Oliver becomes the male equivalent of the traditional &quot;[[damsel in distress]]&quot;, being rescued by Buffy or Merrick on several occasions.  However, their relationship gradually becomes romantic and Oliver becomes her partner in fighting the undead.

After several successful outings, Buffy is drawn into conflict with a local vampire king named Lothos ([[Rutger Hauer]]), who has killed a number of past Slayers. Lothos eventually kills Merrick as well, giving her the motivation she needs to face him in battle. They eventually clash during the middle of the senior dance at Buffy's high school. Through the use of her own unconventional methods, she is able to defeat Lothos and his minions.

==Cast==
